Key Match Events: C. Gakpo scored for the Netherlands in the 47th minute.
M. Depay scored for the Netherlands in the 75th minute.
D. Malen scored an own goal in the 6th minute.
R. Schmid scored for Austria in the 59th minute.
M. Sabitzer scored the winning goal for Austria in the 80th minute.
Pentz made a crucial save against Van de Ven in the 90+3rd minute.
Weghorst headed over the crossbar in the 86th minute.
Baumgartner's goal was disallowed for offside in the 83rd minute.
Sabitzer's goal in the 80th minute was a brilliant left-footed strike into the roof of the net.
Post-Match Reflections: Austria's victory means they finished top of Group D.
Depay is closing in on the Netherlands' goal record.
Austria will face the runners up in Group F in the next round.
The Netherlands could face England in the last 16 if England wins Group C.
Austria's performance has marked them as dark horses in the tournament.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Marcel Sabitzer was awarded UEFA's Player of the Match.
Austria's place as Group D winners was confirmed after France drew 1-1 with Poland.
The match was described as a rollercoaster and potentially the game of the tournament so far.
